1
00:00:02,461 --> 00:00:03,504
[GASPS]

2
00:00:03,670 --> 00:00:05,130
OLIVER:
<i>The day I went missing...</i>

3
00:00:09,301 --> 00:00:11,637
<i>...was the day I died.</i>

4
00:00:12,804 --> 00:00:15,182
<i>Five years in hell
forged me into a weapon...</i>

5
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:18,227
<i>...which I use to honor a vow
I made to my father...</i>

6
00:00:18,393 --> 00:00:21,647
<i>...who sacrificed his life for mine.</i>

7
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:24,650
<i>In his final moments,
he told me the truth...</i>

8
00:00:25,192 --> 00:00:29,071
<i>...that our family's wealth had been
built on the suffering of others.</i>

9
00:00:29,238 --> 00:00:30,697
<i>That he failed our city...</i>

10
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:33,867
<i>...and that it was up to me
to save it and right his wrongs.</i>

11
00:00:34,993 --> 00:00:38,372
<i>But to do that without endangering
the people closest to me...</i>

12
00:00:38,539 --> 00:00:40,374
<i>...I have to be someone else.</i>

13
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:43,961
<i>I have to be something else.</i>

14
00:00:44,127 --> 00:00:46,630
MAN 1:
Who's that? Where'd he come from?

15
00:00:46,797 --> 00:00:48,340
[GRUNTING]

16
00:00:50,259 --> 00:00:53,762
MAN 2:
What's going on here?

17
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:56,723
MAN 3:
Get the chopper back, now.

18
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:58,225
MAN 4:
Who is this guy?

19
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:03,605
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Please, wait, wait.

20
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:10,320
No, please.

21
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:13,198
Marcus Redmond, you've failed this city.

22
00:01:13,365 --> 00:01:14,866
Please, don't. Please. Don't.

23
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:17,202
Cell phone, inside pocket,
call your partner.

24
00:01:17,369 --> 00:01:20,205
Tell him to give those pensioners
back their money.

25
00:01:20,372 --> 00:01:23,875
-Please, don't.
-Do it now.

26
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:30,549
MAN [OVER TV]: <i>Over the past 15 years,
Mr. Redmond has withdrawn...</i>

27
00:01:30,716 --> 00:01:33,427
<i>...more than 30 million dollars
from the plan's account.</i>

28
00:01:33,594 --> 00:01:37,556
<i>Mr. Redmond claims refunding the Halcyon
pension plan has always been his intent.</i>

29
00:01:37,723 --> 00:01:41,059
<i>But sources say Redmond
was coerced by the vigilante.</i>

30
00:01:41,268 --> 00:01:44,103
This guy gets more airtime
than the Kardashians, right?

31
00:01:44,313 --> 00:01:46,982
Five years on an island and
you still know who they are.

32
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:50,902
Been catching up. It's nice to see
our culture has improved while I was away.

33
00:01:51,069 --> 00:01:53,739
The city used to be different.
People used to feel safe.

34
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:56,617
Oh. What's the matter, Mom?
Afraid we're gonna be next?

35
00:01:56,908 --> 00:01:58,994
WALTER:
Do you have any questions, Oliver?

36
00:01:59,161 --> 00:02:03,248
It's a simple proof of life declaration.
Read out a brief statement to the judge...

37
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:06,084
...and your death in absentia
judgment will be voided.

38
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:08,337
It's fine.
I've been in a courtroom before.

39
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:10,631
Four times by my estimate.
There's the DUI.

40
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:12,758
The assault on that paparazzi
douche bag.

41
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:16,511
Stealing that taxi, which was awesome,
by the way.

42
00:02:16,678 --> 00:02:19,181
And who could forget peeing on the cop?

43
00:02:19,431 --> 00:02:22,726
-I wish everyone would.
-I'd hang, but we're headed to court.

44
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:25,729
It's why I'm here. My best friend
is getting resurrected?

45
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:28,982
-I wouldn't miss this for the world.
-What about you?

46
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:32,277
I think the first four times of you
in court was enough for me.

47
00:02:33,028 --> 00:02:34,946
Fair enough.

48
00:02:36,114 --> 00:02:38,700
Mrs. Queen, car's ready.

49
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:44,831
TOMMY:
Walter.

50
00:02:45,874 --> 00:02:48,126
REPORTER 1:
Mr. Queen. Mr. Queen.

51
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:49,461
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

52
00:02:49,628 --> 00:02:52,506
How does it feel to return to civilization
after five years?

53
00:02:52,673 --> 00:02:55,133
REPORTER 2: What happened on that island,
Mr. Queen?

54
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,510
[SCREAMING]

55
00:02:56,677 --> 00:02:59,012
REPORTER 3: Tell us about the accident.
REPORTER 4: Oliver...

56
00:03:00,972 --> 00:03:02,474
[SCREAMING]

57
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:05,977
OLIVER:
There was a storm.

58
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:08,730
The boat went down.

59
00:03:09,356 --> 00:03:11,733
I was the only survivor.

60
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:15,278
-She's not there.
-Sara.

61
00:03:18,407 --> 00:03:19,866
My father didn't make it.

62
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,743
OLIVER:
No.

63
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:25,080
I almost died. I...

64
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:28,959
I thought that I had because I spent...

65
00:03:29,126 --> 00:03:34,005
...so many days on that life raft
before I saw the island.

66
00:03:35,757 --> 00:03:37,551
When I reached it, I knew...

67
00:03:38,427 --> 00:03:42,764
...I knew that I was gonna have to
live for both of us.

68
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:51,148
And in those five years,
it was that one thought...

69
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:53,233
...that kept me going.

70
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:56,194
Your Honor, we move to
vitiate the death-in-absentia...

71
00:03:56,361 --> 00:04:00,574
...filed after Oliver's disappearance at sea
aboard the <i>Queen's Gambit</i> five years ago.

72
00:04:00,741 --> 00:04:04,578
Unfortunately, we will not be requesting
that the declaration of death filed...

73
00:04:04,745 --> 00:04:08,081
...for the petitioner's father,
Robert Queen, be rescinded.

74
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:11,626
The Queen family is only entitled
to one miracle, I'm afraid.

75
00:04:15,547 --> 00:04:18,717
Now on to the offices.
Everyone is waiting to meet you there.

76
00:04:18,884 --> 00:04:21,219
Mom, that was, uh...

77
00:04:21,386 --> 00:04:24,139
A little bit heavier
than I was expecting it to be.

78
00:04:24,306 --> 00:04:27,184
Could we do that tomorrow? Please?

79
00:04:29,561 --> 00:04:31,605
-Of course.
-Thank you.

80
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:39,488
Last week you couldn't wait
to get to the company.

81
00:04:39,696 --> 00:04:42,199
Tommy, I spent five years
away from civilization.

82
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,284
I wasn't exactly thinking straight.

83
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:46,787
-Hi.
-Hi.

84
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:48,538
What are you doing here?

85
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:52,584
Oh, they were bringing me back
from the dead. Legally speaking.

86
00:04:54,085 --> 00:04:56,254
-What are you doing here?
-My job.

87
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:59,591
-Right.
-More like the DA's.

88
00:05:01,885 --> 00:05:04,262
-Hi. Oliver Queen.
-Emily Nocenti.

89
00:05:04,471 --> 00:05:06,848
Oliver just got back from five years
on an island.

90
00:05:07,098 --> 00:05:09,434
Before that,
he was cheating on me with my sister.

91
00:05:09,643 --> 00:05:13,313
He was with her when she died. Last week,
he told me to stay away from him.

92
00:05:13,522 --> 00:05:15,982
It was really good advice. Excuse me.

93
00:05:18,443 --> 00:05:20,654
-It was nice to meet you.
-Yeah, let's go.

94
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:28,870
Come on, buddy.
Shake it off. Let's go.

95
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:32,457
REPORTER 1:
<i>Mr. Somers. One question, sir.</i>

96
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:36,503
I don't know what I've done to earn this
witch hunt from Ms. Lance...

97
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:41,049
...and her bosses at the CNRI, but I can
tell you this. I am an honest businessman...

98
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:44,886
...and I will fight this slander
to my last dime and breath.

99
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:46,930
That's all I have to say. Thank you.

100
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:49,641
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

101
00:05:49,808 --> 00:05:53,436
REPORTER 2: Oh, there's Mr. Queen.
REPORTER 3: Do you want to follow up?

102
00:05:53,603 --> 00:05:55,730
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

103
00:05:55,897 --> 00:05:57,983
REPORTER 4: Tell us what happened inside,
Mr. Queen.

104
00:05:58,149 --> 00:05:59,776
Step back everybody, please.

105
00:05:59,943 --> 00:06:01,820
REPORTER 4:
Can you give us a couple comments?

106
00:06:01,987 --> 00:06:04,781
REPORTER 5: Before you go, sir.
REPORTER 4: Comments about the island?

107
00:06:04,948 --> 00:06:06,449
-What happened?
-Step back.

108
00:06:06,658 --> 00:06:08,827
Hey man, I'll make you
swallow that Nikon. Back.

109
00:06:08,994 --> 00:06:10,787
[TIRES SQUEALING]

110
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:15,083
This happens to you a lot, doesn't it?

111
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:20,881
How much is a life worth?
A life of a man, a good man.

112
00:06:21,047 --> 00:06:24,759
A stevedore on the docks of the city
in which we live.

113
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:27,386
<i>A father.</i>

114
00:06:27,679 --> 00:06:31,808
A man with a daughter. The plaintiff will
prove by a preponderance of evidence...

115
00:06:31,975 --> 00:06:36,354
...that Victor Nocenti learned that his boss,
that man, sitting there, Martin Somers...

116
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:40,859
...was taking bribes from the Chinese
triads to smuggle drugs into our city.

117
00:06:41,026 --> 00:06:43,445
<i>When Victor
threatened to tell the police...</i>

118
00:06:43,612 --> 00:06:46,239
<i>...Martin Somers had him killed.</i>

119
00:06:46,405 --> 00:06:48,909
Mr. Somers is very well-connected...

120
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:51,703
...and has friends
in the District Attorney's office.

121
00:06:52,287 --> 00:06:55,916
Which is why if Emily Nocenti
is to get justice for her father's death...

122
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:58,585
...if Somers is to get justice
for his crimes...

123
00:06:58,752 --> 00:07:01,046
...then someone is gonna have to do it
for them.

124
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:14,976
OLIVER:
<i>Martin Somers.</i>

125
00:07:15,226 --> 00:07:17,771
<i>Laurel's targeted
the worst of Starling City...</i>

126
00:07:17,938 --> 00:07:21,900
<i>...so it's no surprise his name
is on my father's list.</i>

127
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:27,739
<i>The city's police and DA
can't stop him or won't.</i>

128
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:31,910
<i>Laurel thinks she's the only one
willing to bring him to justice.</i>

129
00:07:33,536 --> 00:07:35,664
<i>She's wrong.</i>

130
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:39,834
You, listen up.

131
00:07:40,085 --> 00:07:43,296
The longer this goes on, the more
the media is gonna crucify me.

132
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:45,548
You shut this trial down,
understand me?

133
00:07:45,757 --> 00:07:47,550
-Yes, sir.
SOMERS: What the hell?

134
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:49,094
[SOMERS CHOKING AND YELLING]

135
00:07:55,016 --> 00:07:57,352
[GASPING THEN CHOKES]

136
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:00,105
[SOMERS GROANING]

137
00:08:00,689 --> 00:08:02,983
GREEN ARROW: Martin Somers...
SOMERS: Who the hell are you?

138
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:05,193
GREEN ARROW: You've failed this city.
-No, no, no.

139
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,403
[ARROW WHOOSHES]

140
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:08,697
GREEN ARROW:
You're going to testify in that trial.

141
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:11,324
You're gonna confess
to having Victor Nocenti killed.

142
00:08:11,491 --> 00:08:12,617
[SOMERS GRUNTING]

143
00:08:12,784 --> 00:08:15,120
There won't be a second warning.

144
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:17,288
[SOMERS YELLING AND GRUNTING]

145
00:08:33,054 --> 00:08:35,181
I hired you to protect my son.

146
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:38,810
I'm not a bodyguard,
but it seems to me the first requirement...

147
00:08:38,977 --> 00:08:42,063
...would be staying next
to the man you're hired to protect.

148
00:08:42,313 --> 00:08:44,858
I've never had a client
who didn't want my protection.

149
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:46,568
I hired you.

150
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:49,320
That makes me the client.

151
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:55,869
Now, where do you think my son is going
on these chaperone-less excursions?

152
00:08:56,036 --> 00:08:59,831
-Ma'am, I truly do not know.
-And he truly doesn't.

153
00:08:59,998 --> 00:09:03,168
Then perhaps you'd like to share with me,
you know, where it is you run off to?

154
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:04,669
[OLIVER CHUCKLES]

155
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:07,088
I've been alone for five years.

156
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:09,174
-I know that, Oliver...
-Mom.

157
00:09:10,508 --> 00:09:12,093
Alone.

158
00:09:13,219 --> 00:09:14,387
I see.

159
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:19,726
I promise to introduce her if it ever gets
to the exchanging first names stage.

160
00:09:19,893 --> 00:09:24,189
I'd rather you promise to take Mr. Diggle
with you on your next rendezvous.

161
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:27,108
It's not safe.
You've already been abducted once.

162
00:09:27,525 --> 00:09:30,195
There is a maniac out
there hunting the wealthy.

163
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:33,073
-That maniac saved my life.
-This isn't a game.

164
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:35,617
I lost you once.

165
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:39,412
And I am not going through that again.

166
00:09:40,955 --> 00:09:42,373
Okay.

167
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:46,211
Dig's my guy.

168
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:49,047
Thank you.

169
00:09:51,674 --> 00:09:53,093
[SIGHS]

170
00:09:53,885 --> 00:09:55,887
Sorry to give you so much grief.

171
00:09:56,971 --> 00:09:59,265
I served three tours in Afghanistan,
Mr. Queen.

172
00:09:59,474 --> 00:10:02,435
You don't even come close
to my definition of grief.

173
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:05,271
I tell you what...

174
00:10:05,855 --> 00:10:09,484
...you ditch me one more time
and no one will have to fire me.

175
00:10:16,241 --> 00:10:20,912
-Where are you going?
-Somewhere loud and smoky.

176
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:23,414
Don't bother trying
to pickpocket my stash...

177
00:10:23,581 --> 00:10:25,500
...because I'm gonna go
get drunk instead.

178
00:10:26,584 --> 00:10:28,128
Thea.

179
00:10:29,379 --> 00:10:32,590
Do you think this is what Dad
would want for you?

180
00:10:33,424 --> 00:10:35,677
Dead people don't want anything.

181
00:10:35,885 --> 00:10:39,305
-It's one of the benefits of being dead.
-I was dead.

182
00:10:40,515 --> 00:10:44,185
-And I wanted a lot.
-Except for your family.

183
00:10:44,811 --> 00:10:47,689
You've been home a week.
And all you do is avoid Mom...

184
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:50,275
...ignore Walter and judge me.

185
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:54,445
Don't wait up.

186
00:10:58,408 --> 00:11:01,327
Well, I owe you an apology, Mr. Somers.

187
00:11:01,536 --> 00:11:03,538
We come all the way down to your docks...

188
00:11:03,705 --> 00:11:05,790
...and turns out
you don't need the police.

189
00:11:05,957 --> 00:11:07,834
Which is exactly what I've been saying.

190
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:11,629
So I guess that 911 call we got last night
from your stevedores saying...

191
00:11:11,838 --> 00:11:14,841
...you were attacked by a guy
in a hood and a bow and arrow.

192
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:16,509
I guess that...

193
00:11:16,675 --> 00:11:17,760
Hm...

194
00:11:17,927 --> 00:11:20,054
Was that a practical joke?

195
00:11:22,056 --> 00:11:25,018
-These guys like to fool around.
-Yeah.

196
00:11:25,185 --> 00:11:26,311
[SCOFFS]

197
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:28,813
You know, I'd be very
inclined to believe an honest...

198
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:31,900
...upstanding businessman like
yourself except...

199
00:11:32,066 --> 00:11:35,153
Well, one of my men...

200
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:38,448
...found this at your docks.

201
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:41,326
You see, there's this vigilante
running around.

202
00:11:41,492 --> 00:11:43,870
He thinks he's some kind of Robin Hood.

203
00:11:44,037 --> 00:11:47,498
Robbing the rich.
Trying to teach them a lesson, I guess...

204
00:11:47,706 --> 00:11:50,668
...I don't know.
But the point is, the man is a killer.

205
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:56,341
And nothing and no one is gonna
stop me from bringing him down.

206
00:11:56,507 --> 00:11:58,218
But like you said...

207
00:12:01,512 --> 00:12:02,847
Huh.

208
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:07,602
...clearly nothing happened
here last night.

209
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:12,065
Isn't this a conflict of interest, Detective?

210
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:14,108
After all, your daughter is suing me.

211
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:18,071
-I'm good at keeping my emotions in check.
-I'm not.

212
00:12:18,238 --> 00:12:23,868
You and your daughter don't wanna find out
what I'm capable of when I get emotional.

213
00:12:27,956 --> 00:12:29,249
[SCOFFS]

214
00:12:47,058 --> 00:12:50,520
As you can see, Oliver,
we've modernized quite a bit.

215
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:55,233
BOTH:
Hi.

216
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:57,402
-Ha, ha, are you enjoying yourself?
-Yes, I am.

217
00:12:57,944 --> 00:13:01,155
WALTER: I remember your father used to
bring you here when you were a boy.

218
00:13:01,406 --> 00:13:02,907
You always were so excited.

219
00:13:03,074 --> 00:13:06,661
-Dad let me drink soda in the office.
-So that's why you enjoyed coming.

220
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:14,460
Queen Consolidated's success of late
is a result of its targeted diversification.

221
00:13:15,169 --> 00:13:18,840
We have been making impressive inroads
in cutting-edge fields like...

222
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:22,051
-...biotech and clean energy...
-That's neat. Excuse me.

223
00:13:22,677 --> 00:13:26,139
Can I get a sparkling water
or something cold, please?

224
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:29,642
Sweetheart, Oliver, Walter
and I have something to discuss with you.

225
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:30,977
Come, please, sit.

226
00:13:31,144 --> 00:13:33,938
Mom, it makes me nervous
when you ask me to sit down.

227
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:39,444
The company is about to break ground
on a site for the Applied Sciences division.

228
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:43,531
And we would like to honor your father
by dedicating the building in his name.

229
00:13:43,698 --> 00:13:45,074
Nice.

230
00:13:45,325 --> 00:13:48,661
MOIRA: And we'd like to make
an announcement at the dedication.

231
00:13:48,827 --> 00:13:51,830
That you will be taking a
leadership position in the company.

232
00:13:51,998 --> 00:13:54,125
-No.
-No. Your, your company.

233
00:13:54,292 --> 00:13:55,960
No. I don't wanna lead anything.

234
00:13:56,127 --> 00:13:59,464
Besides, Walter's doing
a very good job here.

235
00:14:00,131 --> 00:14:03,051
You said that you wanted
to be a different person.

236
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:05,887
And you are Robert Queen's son.

237
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:09,307
-I don't need to be reminded of that.
-Obviously, you do.

238
00:14:13,478 --> 00:14:17,815
Everyone here understands that
this transition is really difficult for you.

239
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:20,151
Thank you, Walter.

240
00:14:21,486 --> 00:14:22,528
Which part though?

241
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:25,990
Everyone fantasizing that I got my MBA
while I was on the island?

242
00:14:26,157 --> 00:14:31,621
Or the fact that my father's CFO
now sleeps down the hall from me?

243
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:44,550
You know, five years ago, your
irresponsibility was somewhat charming.

244
00:14:46,344 --> 00:14:48,930
It is a lot less so now.

245
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:03,403
REPORTER:
There he is.

246
00:15:03,653 --> 00:15:05,279
[ALL SHOUTING AND CLAMORING]

247
00:15:15,373 --> 00:15:17,708
The driver will be here in a minute.

248
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,753
Okay.

249
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:24,257
I spent the first 27 years
of my life in Starling City...

250
00:15:24,424 --> 00:15:27,802
...and the next five in Afghanistan.
You want to know what I learned?

251
00:15:28,428 --> 00:15:30,972
There's no place like home?

252
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:32,723
No, just the opposite.

253
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:36,394
Home is a battlefield.

254
00:15:36,561 --> 00:15:38,896
Back home, they're all trying to get you.

255
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:43,443
Get you to open up, be somebody
you're not sure you are anymore.

256
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:49,782
Or I could be wrong. Maybe after
five years alone, you're not as messed up...

257
00:15:49,991 --> 00:15:52,243
...in the head as you have
every right to be.

258
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:59,083
[SEAGULLS SQUAWKING]

259
00:16:00,334 --> 00:16:03,421
Hey. Hey, get away.

260
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:07,425
Hey.

261
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,599
Dad?

262
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:27,069
[GRUNTS]

263
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:28,946
[RETCHING]

264
00:16:31,741 --> 00:16:35,161
Hey. Hey, stay away from him.

265
00:16:39,457 --> 00:16:41,375
[GAGGING]

266
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:45,463
[GASPING]

267
00:16:56,349 --> 00:16:58,142
[GRUNTING]

268
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:10,988
JOANNA: Well, we anticipate
that Somers' attorney will...

269
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:16,077
...try and paint you as blinded by grief
or looking to make a buck.

270
00:17:16,285 --> 00:17:19,539
But this isn't about the money.
I just want justice for my father.

271
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:23,584
Emily, there are a lot of people
who don't want this trial to proceed.

272
00:17:23,793 --> 00:17:25,711
-Dangerous people.
-My mother died...

273
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:29,090
...when I was a baby. My father
is the only family I've ever known.

274
00:17:29,340 --> 00:17:30,925
And they slit his throat.

275
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:35,680
They are going to have to kill me
if they want me to give this up.

276
00:17:35,846 --> 00:17:39,892
-Well, let's hope it doesn't come to that.
LANCE: And it won't.

277
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:43,896
-What's going on?
-You three are getting police protection.

278
00:17:44,105 --> 00:17:47,024
Get used to their faces,
they're going with you everywhere.

279
00:17:47,191 --> 00:17:49,944
-No arguments.
-I'm a lawyer. I live to argue.

280
00:17:50,111 --> 00:17:52,530
I'm your father.
I live to keep you safe.

281
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:57,034
-Emily, let's go grab a cup of coffee?
-Yes, why not do that? Thank you.

282
00:17:57,201 --> 00:18:00,454
Please, go with them. Stay there.

283
00:18:01,914 --> 00:18:06,586
Protective custody? I seem to recall you
trying that once I discovered boys.

284
00:18:06,752 --> 00:18:09,922
-It didn't work then, either.
-This isn't a joke, Laurel.

285
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:12,383
Martin Somers got attacked last night.

286
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:14,594
-What?
-Yeah.

287
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,262
-By who?
-Doesn't matter.

288
00:18:16,429 --> 00:18:19,056
You have whipped up a storm
with these guys...

289
00:18:19,223 --> 00:18:21,892
...and until the dust settles,
you will be protected.

290
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:23,978
End of discussion.

291
00:18:24,145 --> 00:18:26,105
That might've worked when I was 8...

292
00:18:26,272 --> 00:18:28,983
-...but it's not gonna work anymore.
-End of discussion.

293
00:18:29,150 --> 00:18:30,318
Doing your job? Great.

294
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:33,571
This is me doing mine. Okay?
Not just as a father, but as a cop.

295
00:18:33,738 --> 00:18:37,491
These people are more dangerous
than you are willing to admit.

296
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:39,785
And you've made them angry.

297
00:18:47,752 --> 00:18:50,254
-Thank you for coming.
-Anything for a friend.

298
00:18:50,421 --> 00:18:53,799
We're not friends. You smuggle drugs.
I let you use my port.

299
00:18:54,008 --> 00:18:55,843
For which you are paid a lot of money.

300
00:18:56,010 --> 00:18:58,429
I don't get paid enough
to have arrows shot at me.

301
00:18:58,596 --> 00:19:00,514
You need to take this guy seriously.

302
00:19:00,681 --> 00:19:03,142
He's a bigger threat
than Nocenti ever was.

303
00:19:03,309 --> 00:19:05,478
Now it's Nocenti's daughter
who's the problem.

304
00:19:05,686 --> 00:19:08,606
Unlike your friend with the hood,
we know where to find her.

305
00:19:08,773 --> 00:19:12,610
Don't be an idiot. Take out Emily Nocenti
and Lance will never let this go.

306
00:19:12,777 --> 00:19:16,947
She won't stop until she burns you,
me and the entire triad to the ground.

307
00:19:18,032 --> 00:19:20,117
Then we kill Ms. Lance.

308
00:19:23,454 --> 00:19:26,832
MAN [OVER TV]:<i>Attorney for shipping
magnate Martin Somers confirmed his client...</i>

309
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:31,295
<i>...has no intention of testifying, maintaining
innocence in the death of Victor Nocenti.</i>

310
00:19:31,504 --> 00:19:33,172
<i>Nocenti's body was found
four weeks ago.</i>

311
00:19:33,339 --> 00:19:35,925
<i>We'll keep you updated
as information becomes available.</i>

312
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:39,553
-Wait, how did you get those?
-Don't you knock?

313
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:42,181
No, wait... Mom said
that there were scars...

314
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:52,650
I'm... Oliver,
what happened to you out there?

315
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:59,240
I don't wanna talk about it.

316
00:20:00,074 --> 00:20:01,575
[SCOFFS]

317
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:04,120
Of course you don't.

318
00:20:04,286 --> 00:20:07,832
You never want to talk to me
about anything except for my social life.

319
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:11,335
Wait. Where are you going?

320
00:20:11,711 --> 00:20:13,546
Why should I tell you?

321
00:20:16,257 --> 00:20:17,591
I'm sorry, Thea.

322
00:20:19,844 --> 00:20:25,266
I need to get better at talking
about what happened to me there.

323
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:31,605
But I'm not ready yet. Okay?

324
00:20:33,691 --> 00:20:37,570
-Do you have a second?
-Yeah.

325
00:20:38,529 --> 00:20:42,575
Good. I wanna show you
something out back.

326
00:20:46,203 --> 00:20:50,332
Sometimes when I felt...whatever.

327
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:52,418
I'd come here.

328
00:20:55,838 --> 00:21:00,301
About a month after the funerals,
Mom stopped going out.

329
00:21:01,218 --> 00:21:03,721
Pretty soon
she stopped talking altogether.

330
00:21:04,722 --> 00:21:08,017
The house got so quiet.
So I'd come here.

331
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:12,062
To talk to you.

332
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:17,777
Stupid stuff.
Like what I was doing that day...

333
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:20,946
...what boy I had a crush on.

334
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:27,411
And then sometimes, I'd ask you, beg you,
to find your way home to me.

335
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:29,246
Now here you are.

336
00:21:30,581 --> 00:21:34,251
And the truth is, I felt closer to you
when you were dead.

337
00:21:35,836 --> 00:21:38,964
Look, I know it was hell where you were.

338
00:21:39,131 --> 00:21:41,634
But it was hell here too.

339
00:21:43,928 --> 00:21:46,305
You gotta let me in, Ollie.

340
00:21:48,057 --> 00:21:51,101
You gotta let someone in.

341
00:22:04,949 --> 00:22:06,033
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

342
00:22:22,633 --> 00:22:25,553
Hi. Are you okay?

343
00:22:25,803 --> 00:22:27,680
There are two cop cars outside.

344
00:22:27,847 --> 00:22:30,975
How am I supposed to stay away from you
if you won't stay away from me?

345
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:34,103
What are you doing here, Ollie?

346
00:22:35,353 --> 00:22:36,897
My sister took, what...

347
00:22:37,064 --> 00:22:40,150
She pointed out that
I have been distant since I got back...

348
00:22:40,317 --> 00:22:45,030
...and that it would probably be a good idea
if I let somebody in.

349
00:22:45,823 --> 00:22:48,909
So you thought you'd start
with the first person you pushed away?

350
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:51,369
I did that to protect you.

351
00:22:51,871 --> 00:22:54,748
And then I saw you yesterday
and I realized that I hurt you.

352
00:22:55,791 --> 00:22:57,668
[SIGHS]

353
00:23:03,674 --> 00:23:05,383
Thank you.

354
00:23:08,971 --> 00:23:10,556
Wow.

355
00:23:10,973 --> 00:23:14,101
This place hasn't changed in five years.

356
00:23:14,935 --> 00:23:17,855
I haven't really had time to redecorate.

357
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:19,857
I'm a jerk.

358
00:23:21,483 --> 00:23:26,280
Before the island, I was a jerk,
and now I'm just a...

359
00:23:26,906 --> 00:23:29,742
-I'm a damaged jerk.
-What's in the bag?

360
00:23:31,827 --> 00:23:33,829
I thought about many things
on the island...

361
00:23:33,996 --> 00:23:36,540
...but there was one thing
I thought about every day.

362
00:23:36,707 --> 00:23:39,710
I actually dreamed about it,
and I promised myself...

363
00:23:39,877 --> 00:23:45,674
...that if I ever got a chance to do it again,
I'd do it with you.

364
00:23:48,761 --> 00:23:50,054
Eat ice cream.

365
00:23:56,143 --> 00:23:58,312
This is as good as I remember.

366
00:24:01,982 --> 00:24:03,901
My mother wants me
to join the company.

367
00:24:04,610 --> 00:24:07,905
Yeah. Take my rightful place.

368
00:24:08,614 --> 00:24:12,409
I can't exactly picture you
as the master of the universe.

369
00:24:15,955 --> 00:24:21,919
You know, after five years, I have plans.

370
00:24:22,711 --> 00:24:24,588
I have things that I have to do.

371
00:24:24,922 --> 00:24:27,465
I can't do that if I'm...

372
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:33,263
I don't know. Attending board meetings
and stockholder briefings.

373
00:24:34,932 --> 00:24:38,852
Oliver. You're an adult.

374
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:41,355
-You can say no.
-Oh, I tried.

375
00:24:42,314 --> 00:24:44,233
Didn't take.

376
00:24:44,441 --> 00:24:49,238
Well, then don't tell her, show her.

377
00:24:49,446 --> 00:24:52,741
Be the person that
you want her to see you as.

378
00:24:53,784 --> 00:24:55,536
Trust me.

379
00:24:56,829 --> 00:24:59,832
I have plenty of experience
with disapproving parents.

380
00:24:59,999 --> 00:25:02,918
I have been on the receiving end
of your father's disapproval.

381
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:06,755
He blames himself
more than he blames you.

382
00:25:07,256 --> 00:25:10,759
He thinks that, you know, maybe if
he and Sara were closer...

383
00:25:10,968 --> 00:25:13,554
...she would have told him
about the boat trip.

384
00:25:14,138 --> 00:25:16,765
And he could have stopped her
from going with you.

385
00:25:17,391 --> 00:25:20,978
-I am sorry.
-You apologized already.

386
00:25:23,397 --> 00:25:25,816
It'll never be enough.

387
00:25:28,569 --> 00:25:29,611
[METAL CLATTERS]

388
00:25:29,778 --> 00:25:32,573
-Did you hear that?
-What?

389
00:25:38,037 --> 00:25:39,872
There's someone on the fire escape.

390
00:25:42,624 --> 00:25:44,293
-What?
-Hey, come on. Come on.

391
00:25:45,502 --> 00:25:46,544
[GRUNTS]

392
00:25:47,588 --> 00:25:49,048
[LAUREL GASPING]

393
00:25:49,256 --> 00:25:50,591
[LAUREL SCREAMS]

394
00:25:53,177 --> 00:25:54,845
[OLIVER GRUNTS AND LAUREL SCREAMS]

395
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:57,848
Huh.

396
00:25:58,932 --> 00:25:59,975
[GUN COCKS]

397
00:26:00,642 --> 00:26:01,727
Unh!

398
00:26:05,189 --> 00:26:06,356
[BOTH GRUNTING]

399
00:26:14,031 --> 00:26:15,157
[DIGGLE GRUNTS]

400
00:26:20,578 --> 00:26:21,747
[WHIMPERS]

401
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:24,666
-Are you hurt?
-No.

402
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:26,752
-Are you hurt, Mr. Queen?
-No. No.

403
00:26:26,919 --> 00:26:29,713
This is why it's a good idea
to have a bodyguard.

404
00:26:31,340 --> 00:26:32,800
Hey, you okay?

405
00:26:37,387 --> 00:26:39,098
[POLICE CHATTER]

406
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:43,727
-Daddy.
-Thank God.

407
00:26:43,894 --> 00:26:46,730
-Thank God. Are you all right?
-I'm okay.

408
00:26:46,897 --> 00:26:48,649
-Yeah.
-Those cops that you put on me.

409
00:26:50,442 --> 00:26:52,236
-They...
-I went to ask for a light...

410
00:26:52,402 --> 00:26:54,113
...and they were both dead
in the squad car.

411
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:58,492
It's all right, honey. It's okay.

412
00:26:58,659 --> 00:27:01,411
Mr. Diggle, thank you.

413
00:27:01,619 --> 00:27:04,622
You feel free to run as many red lights
as you want.

414
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:07,876
-I was doing my job, sir.
-No, your job is protecting him.

415
00:27:09,586 --> 00:27:12,965
It seems like whenever you're
with one of my daughters, people die.

416
00:27:13,257 --> 00:27:14,800
You stay away from Laurel, or...

417
00:27:14,967 --> 00:27:17,427
...the next time you disappear,
it'll be permanent.

418
00:27:17,594 --> 00:27:18,679
-Dad.
-No, Laurel...

419
00:27:18,887 --> 00:27:21,890
It's okay. I understand.

420
00:27:23,100 --> 00:27:25,102
Yeah.

421
00:27:25,602 --> 00:27:27,437
Laurel.

422
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:34,278
I'd say thank you
but I don't think that'd cover it.

423
00:27:34,486 --> 00:27:36,989
Like I told your cop friend,
I was just doing my job.

424
00:27:37,156 --> 00:27:39,700
Besides, I think it should be you
that I'm thanking.

425
00:27:44,288 --> 00:27:45,622
-What for?
-The knife.

426
00:27:46,790 --> 00:27:47,916
The knife.

427
00:27:48,125 --> 00:27:50,127
-I got lucky.
-That was a kitchen knife.

428
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:51,461
It wasn't weighted properly.

429
00:27:51,628 --> 00:27:53,547
You threw it for accuracy
across a ten-foot room.

430
00:27:53,714 --> 00:27:55,799
Exactly. I got lucky.

431
00:27:55,966 --> 00:27:58,051
I'm not the man you want
to take for a fool.

432
00:27:58,218 --> 00:28:00,804
-You understand me?
-Yes.

433
00:28:00,971 --> 00:28:04,183
I think I'm just beginning to
understand the kind of man you are.

434
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:06,143
Shouldn't take you very long.

435
00:28:06,310 --> 00:28:08,228
I'm shallow.

436
00:28:08,437 --> 00:28:09,980
And very tired. So...

437
00:28:12,983 --> 00:28:14,026
Good night.

438
00:28:16,820 --> 00:28:17,988
Good night, sir.

439
00:28:24,244 --> 00:28:27,039
OLIVER: <i>I wanted to give
Martin Somers the chance to confess...</i>

440
00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:30,209
<i>...and face a court,
but he chose to go after someone...</i>

441
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:32,836
<i>...I care about instead.</i>

442
00:28:36,215 --> 00:28:38,884
<i>He's still going to face justice.</i>

443
00:28:39,051 --> 00:28:42,095
<i>It'll just be a different kind.</i>

444
00:28:46,016 --> 00:28:48,518
That triad bitch screwed up
the hit on Lance.

445
00:28:48,685 --> 00:28:51,605
Now the triad is gonna erase
every ounce of evidence...

446
00:28:51,772 --> 00:28:53,982
...of their smuggling operation.
Including me.

447
00:28:54,191 --> 00:28:55,692
Except that's not gonna happen.

448
00:28:55,859 --> 00:28:58,528
Tell Wallace to get the boat ready.
I'm leaving tonight.

449
00:28:58,695 --> 00:29:02,699
Wallace? Wallace, you copy?

450
00:29:02,866 --> 00:29:04,034
Wallace?

451
00:29:04,201 --> 00:29:06,703
GREEN ARROW:
<i>Wallace isn't here.</i>

452
00:29:06,870 --> 00:29:08,705
<i>But I am.</i>

453
00:29:08,872 --> 00:29:10,040
We need to move. Now.

454
00:29:10,540 --> 00:29:12,417
-Move.
BODYGUARD: Sir, we got six men out there.

455
00:29:12,584 --> 00:29:14,044
SOMERS:
That's not enough. Move it..

456
00:29:14,211 --> 00:29:16,964
You're going into that court room
to recuse yourself.

457
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:19,216
Or drop it, but either way you are done.

458
00:29:19,383 --> 00:29:21,301
If you think I'm gonna abandon
Emily...

459
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:22,970
...you don't know me that well.

460
00:29:23,136 --> 00:29:26,223
You don't know me well, young lady.
I will lock you in a cell.

461
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:28,392
Well, I guess
that's what it's gonna take then.

462
00:29:31,061 --> 00:29:34,606
Damn it, Laurel. I thought after
what happened with Sara...

463
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:36,900
...that you'd stop being just so reckless.

464
00:29:37,067 --> 00:29:40,445
It's not about being reckless,
it's just the opposite.

465
00:29:41,238 --> 00:29:43,657
I'm trying to make this city safer.
Just like you.

466
00:29:45,284 --> 00:29:50,664
Sweetie, you're my only daughter, Laurel.

467
00:29:51,415 --> 00:29:56,169
-You're all I have left to live for.
-But what you want for me isn't living.

468
00:29:56,420 --> 00:29:58,755
Having cops around,
not being able to do my job.

469
00:29:58,922 --> 00:30:02,092
Your job is not going after people
like the triad or Somers.

470
00:30:02,259 --> 00:30:04,928
My job is to use the law to fight
for what is right.

471
00:30:05,595 --> 00:30:09,683
-Just like you taught me.
-Well, that's dirty. Using me against me.

472
00:30:11,101 --> 00:30:13,103
You can't do that.

473
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:16,440
Well...

474
00:30:17,316 --> 00:30:19,609
...maybe I picked that up
along the way too.

475
00:30:21,611 --> 00:30:23,113
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

476
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:29,161
-Lance.
MAN: <i>Sir, we got a report from the wharf site.</i>

477
00:30:29,328 --> 00:30:31,830
<i>-Somer's imports.</i>
LANCE: I'll be right there.

478
00:30:33,290 --> 00:30:34,458
I've gotta go.

479
00:30:34,624 --> 00:30:36,710
There's something going on at the docks.

480
00:30:37,878 --> 00:30:39,629
[AUTOMATIC GUN FIRE]

481
00:30:45,802 --> 00:30:47,054
[MAN GRUNTS]

482
00:30:51,224 --> 00:30:52,601
[GREEN ARROW GRUNTS]

483
00:31:01,777 --> 00:31:03,070
[YELLS]

484
00:31:09,659 --> 00:31:10,702
GREEN ARROW:
Somers.

485
00:31:14,873 --> 00:31:16,166
[SOMERS GASPING]

486
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:18,460
[YELLS]

487
00:31:20,712 --> 00:31:21,797
[SOMERS GRUNTS]

488
00:31:21,963 --> 00:31:23,298
Oh, God, no, no, no.

489
00:31:23,465 --> 00:31:25,467
He can't help you.

490
00:31:26,635 --> 00:31:28,720
I want the truth about Victor Nocenti.

491
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:32,974
-I can't. The triad will kill me.
-The triad's not your concern right now.

492
00:31:34,101 --> 00:31:35,602
[YELLING AND GASPING]

493
00:31:35,977 --> 00:31:39,314
All right. All right, all right.
It wasn't me that killed him.

494
00:31:39,481 --> 00:31:43,193
-It was the triad.
-Acting on whose instructions?

495
00:31:45,487 --> 00:31:47,572
-Whose?
-All right, all right. It was mine.

496
00:31:47,781 --> 00:31:49,032
It was mine, all right?

497
00:31:49,199 --> 00:31:52,661
Nocenti said
he was gonna testify against me.

498
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:56,164
[IN CHINESE]

499
00:31:56,331 --> 00:31:57,791
[IN CHINESE]

500
00:31:57,999 --> 00:31:59,209
[BOTH GRUNTING]

501
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:09,177
[SIRENS BLARING]

502
00:32:27,446 --> 00:32:29,865
MAN [OVER SPEAKER]: <i>It's the police.
Drop your weapons.</i>

503
00:32:30,031 --> 00:32:32,868
<i>You're surrounded.
Come out with your hands on your head.</i>

504
00:32:41,543 --> 00:32:43,211
Freeze.

505
00:32:46,756 --> 00:32:49,384
You twitch and you're dead.

506
00:32:55,223 --> 00:32:57,851
Bow down, hands up.

507
00:33:17,746 --> 00:33:20,165
SOMER [OVER RECORDING]:
<i>It was mine. It was mine, all right?</i>

508
00:33:20,373 --> 00:33:23,960
<i>Nocenti said
he was gonna testify against me.</i>

509
00:33:24,127 --> 00:33:26,171
Son of a bitch.

510
00:33:26,421 --> 00:33:27,672
[SIRENS BLARING]

511
00:33:36,515 --> 00:33:38,433
<i>Laurel was right.</i>

512
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:41,478
<i>I can't be the Oliver
my mother wants me to be...</i>

513
00:33:41,645 --> 00:33:45,106
<i>...and still keep the promise
I made to my father.</i>

514
00:33:47,317 --> 00:33:50,779
<i>I have to be the person
I need them to see me as.</i>

515
00:33:53,782 --> 00:33:55,325
[CHATTERING]

516
00:33:55,659 --> 00:33:58,370
Okay, this is a surprise.

517
00:33:58,537 --> 00:34:02,791
-Did you show up here by mistake?
-By invitation.

518
00:34:03,124 --> 00:34:05,126
-Oh...
-Oliver invited me last night.

519
00:34:05,293 --> 00:34:09,130
-Last night?
-Is that surprise or jealousy I'm hearing?

520
00:34:09,297 --> 00:34:11,967
Look, I just don't want him
to find out anything, okay?

521
00:34:13,552 --> 00:34:17,639
-Oliver has been through a lot.
-Tommy, we've all been through a lot.

522
00:34:17,806 --> 00:34:21,142
Good afternoon
and thank you all for coming.

523
00:34:21,309 --> 00:34:25,647
Welcome to the future site of the Robert
Queen Memorial Applied Sciences Center.

524
00:34:28,817 --> 00:34:31,486
Now this is a building that will stand
as a monument...

525
00:34:31,653 --> 00:34:35,323
...to the man whose company
and vision are his greatest legacies.

526
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:37,409
OLIVER:
Whoa! Whoa.

527
00:34:39,619 --> 00:34:41,246
Mm.

528
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:48,336
What about me? Right? I'm a legacy.

529
00:34:48,503 --> 00:34:53,258
Hey, thanks for warming them up, Walt.
All right. Fine, fine. Shovel. I got it.

530
00:34:53,508 --> 00:34:54,676
Whoa! Oh.

531
00:34:54,884 --> 00:34:58,555
I'm kidding. I'm kidding.
I got it. I got it.

532
00:34:58,722 --> 00:35:01,349
Some of you may not know me.
My name is Oliver Queen.

533
00:35:06,021 --> 00:35:10,066
Watch some television, read a newspaper,
I'm kind of famous right now.

534
00:35:10,233 --> 00:35:14,696
Mostly, though, I'm famous
because I'm Robert Queen's son.

535
00:35:14,863 --> 00:35:21,536
Uh, but as Walter, who's my new dad...
Huh? Who is... Sorry.

536
00:35:21,703 --> 00:35:27,751
As Walter was saying,
I'm not much of a legacy, per se, and...

537
00:35:27,917 --> 00:35:32,589
-Oliver, you don't have to do this...
-No, sit. Sit. Gosh.

538
00:35:33,548 --> 00:35:35,800
See, I was supposed to come here today...

539
00:35:36,009 --> 00:35:39,554
...and I'm supposed to take
my rightful place at the company.

540
00:35:40,096 --> 00:35:44,559
Prodigal son returns home
and becomes the heir apparent.

541
00:35:47,729 --> 00:35:49,397
But I'm not my father.

542
00:35:50,565 --> 00:35:54,986
I'm not the man he was.
I'm not half the man he was.

543
00:35:55,153 --> 00:36:01,785
I never will be.
So, please, stop asking me to be.

544
00:36:04,996 --> 00:36:06,706
[PEOPLE WHISPERING]

545
00:36:27,143 --> 00:36:29,604
MAN [OVER TV]:
<i>Martin Somers, CEO of Starling Port...</i>

546
00:36:29,771 --> 00:36:31,898
<i>...arrested for the murder of Victor Nocenti.</i>

547
00:36:32,065 --> 00:36:37,487
<i>He is also being accused of accepting cash,
including over ten million in bribes.</i>

548
00:36:38,154 --> 00:36:41,991
We can pursue the civil suit if you want,
but the DA now has no choice...

549
00:36:42,158 --> 00:36:44,494
...with Mr. Somers' confession,
to prosecute him.

550
00:36:44,661 --> 00:36:47,205
He's going to jail, Emily.
For the rest of his life.

551
00:36:47,372 --> 00:36:49,499
Thank you so much for fighting for us.

552
00:36:49,666 --> 00:36:52,711
Well, thank you for being brave enough
to let me.

553
00:36:59,551 --> 00:37:00,927
Hey.

554
00:37:01,094 --> 00:37:03,680
I thought I didn't need
police protection anymore.

555
00:37:03,847 --> 00:37:05,849
I thought I didn't need a reason
to see my daughter.

556
00:37:06,015 --> 00:37:07,517
You don't.

557
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:13,690
Hm. You look tired.

558
00:37:13,857 --> 00:37:16,735
I was filling out reports
on the shoot-out at the port...

559
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:20,864
...and getting grilled about
how I let that archer get away.

560
00:37:21,030 --> 00:37:23,742
I have to admit, I'm kind of glad he did.

561
00:37:23,908 --> 00:37:25,869
He brought down Martin Somers.

562
00:37:26,035 --> 00:37:29,372
He hurt a bunch of people doing it.
He is no hero. He's an anarchist.

563
00:37:29,539 --> 00:37:33,710
Yeah, well, whoever he is,
it seems like he's trying to help.

564
00:37:33,877 --> 00:37:36,296
The city doesn't need that help.
I always told you...

565
00:37:36,463 --> 00:37:38,298
...you don't go outside the law
to find justice.

566
00:37:38,506 --> 00:37:43,261
No, I believe that, all right?
And I promise you, when I catch this guy...

567
00:37:43,428 --> 00:37:45,388
<i>...he's gonna believe it too.</i>

568
00:38:12,332 --> 00:38:14,459
[PANTING]

569
00:39:04,133 --> 00:39:06,219
Well, you saw for yourself.

570
00:39:07,345 --> 00:39:09,347
My son knows nothing.

571
00:39:09,514 --> 00:39:12,642
Robert didn't tell him anything
that could hurt us.

572
00:39:12,809 --> 00:39:16,688
He has no idea
that the yacht was sabotaged.

573
00:39:39,377 --> 00:39:41,754
All that time on the island,
plotting my return...

574
00:39:41,921 --> 00:39:46,509
...I didn't realize
how hard it would be...

575
00:39:46,926 --> 00:39:52,181
...to reconnect with Mom, Thea...

576
00:39:53,933 --> 00:39:56,394
...Laurel. Okay, I didn't...

577
00:40:00,148 --> 00:40:04,027
I didn't know how painful it would be
to keep my secrets.

578
00:40:05,778 --> 00:40:10,533
You asked me to save the city.
To right your wrongs.

579
00:40:10,700 --> 00:40:12,368
I will.

580
00:40:13,411 --> 00:40:15,371
I swear.

581
00:40:17,957 --> 00:40:23,713
But to do that, I can't be the Oliver
that everyone wants me to be...

582
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:26,382
...which means that sometimes...

583
00:40:27,592 --> 00:40:30,053
...to honor your wishes...

584
00:40:33,056 --> 00:40:36,100
...I need to dishonor your memory.

585
00:40:36,726 --> 00:40:38,811
I'm sorry.

586
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:45,944
Take it down.

587
00:40:53,910 --> 00:40:56,245
Will you be going out tonight, sir?

588
00:40:58,122 --> 00:41:00,124
Definitely.

589
00:41:17,183 --> 00:41:18,434
[ARROW WHOOSHES]

590
00:41:18,601 --> 00:41:20,103
[SCREAMING]

